{
  "mcpServers": {
    "radarr_sonarr": {
      "command": "uv",
      "args": [
        "--directory", "/path/to/radarr-sonarr-mcp",
        "run", "radarr_sonarr_mcp/server.py"
      ],
      "env": {
        "NAS_IP": "10.0.0.23",
        "RADARR_PORT": "7878",
        "SONARR_PORT": "8989",
        "LIDARR_PORT": "8686",
        "RADARR_API_KEY": "your_radarr_api_key",
        "SONARR_API_KEY": "your_sonarr_api_key",
        "LIDARR_API_KEY": "your_lidarr_api_key",
        "MCP_SERVER_PORT": "3000",
        "JELLYFIN_BASE_URL": "http://10.0.0.23:5055",
        "JELLYFIN_API_KEY": "your_jellyfin_api_key",
        "JELLYFIN_USER_ID": "your_jellyfin_user_id",
        "PLEX_BASE_URL": "http://10.0.0.23:32400",
        "PLEX_TOKEN": "your_plex_token",
        "TRAKT_CLIENT_ID": "your_trakt_client_id",
        "TRAKT_ACCESS_TOKEN": "your_trakt_access_token",
        "TRAKT_CLIENT_SECRET": "your_trakt_client_secret"
      }
    }
  }
}

## Trakt.tv Setup Instructions

1. Go to https://trakt.tv/oauth/applications
2. Create a new application
3. Use these redirect URIs: `urn:ietf:wg:oauth:2.0:oob` (for manual token)
4. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret
5. Set TRAKT_CLIENT_ID in your environment
6. For personalized features (recommendations, watch history):
   - Generate an access token using OAuth
   - Set TRAKT_ACCESS_TOKEN in your environment

## Watch Status Priority

The server checks watch status in this order:
1. Trakt (most reliable if configured)
2. Jellyfin
3. Plex

If any service reports a movie/show as watched, it's considered watched.
